commands.name: tar
commands.description: GNU 'tar' saves many files together into a single tape or disk archive, and can
examples: tar -cf archive.tar foo bar  # Create archive.tar from files foo and bar.
tar -tvf archive.tar         # List all files in archive.tar verbosely.
tar -xf archive.tar          # Extract all files from archive.tar.
-A, --catenate, --concatenate   append tar files to an archive
